@notice Encode project details into a token ID
@param projectId The project ID (max 232 bits)
@param vintage The vintage year (max 16 bits, e.g., 2024)
@param category The carbon category (max 8 bits, 0-5)
@return tokenId The encoded token ID

@notice Decode a token ID into its components
@param tokenId The token ID to decode
@return projectId The project ID
@return vintage The vintage year
@return category The carbon category

@notice Register a new carbon credit project
@param name Project name
@param methodology Verification methodology (e.g., "VCS", "Gold Standard")
@param verifier Verification body name
@param location Project location
@param category Carbon credit category
@param vintage Vintage year
@return projectId The assigned project ID

@notice Verify a project and set its quality score
@param projectId The project to verify
@param qualityScore Quality score (0-100)

@notice Mint carbon credits for a verified project
@param to Recipient address
@param projectId The project ID
@param amount Amount of carbon credits (in wei, 1e18 = 1 tonne)

@notice Batch mint carbon credits for multiple projects
@param to Recipient address
@param projectIds Array of project IDs
@param amounts Array of amounts

@notice Retire (burn) carbon credits
@param tokenId The token ID to retire
@param amount Amount to retire (in wei)
@param retirementNote Optional note for retirement certificate

@notice Batch retire multiple carbon credits
@param tokenIds Array of token IDs
@param amounts Array of amounts
@param retirementNote Note for all retirements

@notice Get project details
@param projectId The project ID
@return project The project struct

@notice Get user's total retired amount for a token
@param user User address
@param tokenId Token ID
@return amount Total retired amount

@notice Get total retired for all users by category
@param user User address
@param category Carbon category
@return total Total retired in that category (across all projects/vintages)

@title CarbonCreditToken
@notice ERC-1155 token representing carbon credits with vintage and category metadata
@dev Token ID encoding: projectId (232 bits) | vintage (16 bits) | category (8 bits)
